.TH SMARTBUILDTMPRPM 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-utils" "SmartMet Build Tools"
.SH NAME
smartbuildtmprpm \- build an RPM from a git revision with a temporary version bump
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smartbuildtmprpm
.RI [ revision " [" directory ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B smartbuildtmprpm
clones the source git repository into a temporary working directory,
checks out the requested revision, runs
.BR smartmkrelease (1)
to create a fresh local version commit
.RB ( "Test version (GIT revision \fIsha\fR)" )
in that temporary tree, and finally builds the RPM with
.BR "make rpm" .
The local commit and tag exist only in the disposable build tree; the
caller's working copy is not modified, and the temporary directory is
removed when the script exits.
.PP
The new version produced by
.BR smartmkrelease (1)
strictly increases over the previous release, so the resulting RPM
can be uploaded to a staging repository without colliding with any
existing tagged release. This is the standard way to produce a
preview or staging build of a tip\(hyof\(hybranch revision.
.PP
.B smartbuildrev
.RB ( smartbuildrev (1))
is the equivalent script
.I without
the version bump and is preferred for reproducing an already\(hytagged
release.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I revision
Git revision to build (tag, branch or commit SHA). Defaults to
.BR HEAD .
.TP
.I directory
Source directory containing the git repository to clone from.
Defaults to the current directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
Staging build of the current checkout:
.PP
.RS 4
smartbuildtmprpm
.RE
.PP
Staging build of an explicit branch:
.PP
.RS 4
smartbuildtmprpm origin/devel
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR smartbuildrev (1),
.BR smartbuild (1),
.BR smartmkrelease (1),
.BR git (1),
.BR make (1),
.BR rpm (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
